---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Rex & Dino" description="Meet Rex, Dino, Atlas, and the full SELKID cast in Maple Forest — story-led learning characters for K-2.">
  <section class="page-hero refined">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Character-led learning</p>
      <h1>Rex reacts. Dino reframes. Children think.</h1>
      <p>Rex &amp; Dino began inside SELKID's story-based learning world and now carry the brand from SEL foundations into AI cognition. They make difficult ideas feel like adventures, not lectures.</p>
    </div>
    <img src="/assets/hero-maple-forest.png" alt="Rex and Dino in Maple Forest" />
  </section>

  <section class="section white">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-heading centered">
        <p class="eyebrow">The cast</p>
        <h2>Six characters, one story world</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="character-grid premium">
        <article><span>Rex</span><h2>The first reaction</h2><p>Curious, fast, emotional, and honest. Rex represents the child's first impulse—trusting the shiny tool, jumping to a conclusion, or asking the brave question.</p></article>
        <article><span>Dino</span><h2>The second thought</h2><p>Dino brings humor, warmth, and reframing. He slows the moment down without turning it into a lesson that feels heavy.</p></article>
        <article><span>Atlas</span><h2>The evidence keeper</h2><p>Atlas Tortoise models verification, patience, and careful judgment—the core human skills children need around AI.</p></article>
        <article><span>Mayor Owl</span><h2>The community guide</h2><p>Classroom rules, group problems, and the shared life of Maple Forest.</p></article>
        <article><span>Mimi Rabbit</span><h2>Speed &amp; common samples</h2><p>Quick movement and the perspective of what is most common — a lens for bias and missing voices.</p></article>
        <article><span>Maple Forest</span><h2>The story world</h2><p>Maple Forest turns abstract ideas into memorable choices—a place built to grow across comics, animation, audiobooks, and classroom media.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="world-band light">
    <div><p class="eyebrow">Inside the comic</p><h2>Where everyday problems become learning adventures.</h2></div>
    <p>Rex &amp; Dino live in Maple Forest—see them discover training data, bias, and human judgment in kid-sized comic stories.</p>
    <img src="/assets/comics/training-data-p1.png" alt="Rex and Dino Training Data comic page" />
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
